🏗️ Project Architecture
Frontend (React)
        │
        │  API Requests (Axios)
        ▼
Backend (Node.js + Express)
        │
        │ Authentication Logic
        ▼
MongoDB Database
🔄 Authentication Flow
User Registration
User registers
      │
      ▼
Password hashed using bcryptjs
      │
      ▼
User stored in MongoDB
      │
      ▼
JWT token generated
      │
      ▼
Token stored in HTTP-only cookie
User Login
User enters email + password
        │
        ▼
Password verified using bcryptjs
        │
        ▼
JWT token generated
        │
        ▼
Token stored in secure cookie
Google Login
User clicks Google Login
        │
        ▼
Google returns credential token
        │
        ▼
Backend verifies token using google-auth-library
        │
        ▼
User created or fetched from database
        │
        ▼
JWT token generated
Password Reset
User requests password reset
        │
        ▼
OTP sent via email
        │
        ▼
User verifies OTP
        │
        ▼
User sets new password
⚙️ Installation
Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Preetesh8485/Modern-Auth-Project.git
Install Backend Dependencies
cd backend
npm install
Install Frontend Dependencies
cd frontend
npm install
🔑 Environment Variables

Create .env files for both backend and frontend.

Backend .env
PORT=5000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_connection_string
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key
SENDER_EMAIL=your_email
EMAIL_PASSWORD=your_email_password
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
Frontend .env
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
▶️ Running the Project
Start Backend
npm run server
Start Frontend
npm run dev
